# FoundryCare Internal Definitions

## Hosting

FoundryCare includes hosting the website on Foundry-managed infrastructure.

This includes:

- Website hosting costs
- Domain and DNS configuration
- SSL certificate management
- Ongoing platform administration

The client does not need to arrange separate hosting or manage technical infrastructure.

## Security & Maintenance

Foundry takes reasonable responsibility for the ongoing technical health of the website.

This may include:

- Monitoring the general availability of the website
- Reviewing key website functionality
- Investigating reported technical issues
- Applying routine platform and maintenance updates
- Resolving issues where practical
- Coordinating repairs when third-party services fail
- Maintaining a custom-branded maintenance page

If a website becomes temporarily unavailable, visitors may be presented with a Foundry-designed maintenance page tailored to the business. This page may include contact information, location details and business-specific messaging.

## Content Updates

FoundryCare includes reasonable content updates to help keep client websites current, accurate and relevant.

This may include:

- Contact detail updates
- Opening hours changes
- Service additions or amendments
- Seasonal promotions and special offers
- Events and announcements
- Staff changes
- Image replacement
- New content supplied by the client

Frequently changing content, major business developments, or substantial additions to the website may require a different approach, process or arrangement.

Significant redesigns, new functionality, major structural changes or substantial content projects may require a separate quote.

## Search & Listing Reviews

Foundry will conduct a periodic review of major online business listings and directories.

This may include:

- Google Business Profile
- Major search engines
- Mapping services
- Relevant business directories

The review focuses on:

- Website links
- Contact information
- Address details
- Opening hours
- General consistency across platforms

Where practical, Foundry will correct inaccurate information and add a website link where one is available.

This review is undertaken once during each six-month FoundryCare period and is not intended as an ongoing listing management service.

## Regular Check-ins

Foundry will make contact with the client approximately every two months during an active FoundryCare subscription.

The purpose of these check-ins is to:

- Confirm business information remains accurate
- Identify opportunities for website updates
- Discuss upcoming changes, events or promotions
- Identify ways the website could work harder for the business

Check-ins will typically be conducted by email.

## Website Archive

Foundry will provide the client with an up-to-date copy of their website approximately every six months during an active FoundryCare subscription.

The archive serves as:

- A current backup of the website
- Evidence of ownership
- A portable copy should the client choose to host the website elsewhere

The archive will be supplied in a reasonable format determined by Foundry.
